50%, which clearly highlights the need for more effective

770
00:46:58.942 --> 00:47:02.682
and personalized treatments and better biomarkers to guide therapy.

771
00:47:04.002 --> 00:47:07.822
MATISSE is a Phase II multicenter, open label, single

772
00:47:07.902 --> 00:47:11.662
arm study, evaluating anti-CD39 therapy with

773
00:47:11.702 --> 00:47:15.642
IPH5201 in combination with neoadjuvant chemotherapy and

774
00:47:15.662 --> 00:47:19.202
perioperative durvalumab in patients with early-stage resectable

775
00:47:19.382 --> 00:47:22.302
non-small cell lung cancer. So I would like to congratulate Dr.

776
00:47:22.342 --> 00:47:24.942
Barlesi and colleagues for undertaking this effort

777
00:47:25.782 --> 00:47:29.322
and for discussing these findings with me in advance of this

778
00:47:29.362 --> 00:47:29.872
conference.

779
00:47:31.502 --> 00:47:35.462
So I think to understand MATISSE, we need to revisit the ATP

780
00:47:35.742 --> 00:47:38.932
adenosine pathway. In the tumor microenvironment,

781
00:47:39.122 --> 00:47:42.412
extracellular ATP is converted into

782
00:47:42.412 --> 00:47:45.982
adenosine via the sequential action of two important

783
00:47:46.022 --> 00:47:49.842
molecules, CD39 and CD73, which can be

784
00:47:49.902 --> 00:47:52.182
expressed on tumor cells and immune cells.

785
00:47:53.042 --> 00:47:56.141
Adenosine is an important immunosuppressive molecule.

786
00:47:56.502 --> 00:48:00.082
It can inhibit immune cell function, can reduce cytokine

787
00:48:00.102 --> 00:48:03.922
production, and can lead to an exhausted immune microenvironment.

788
00:48:06.022 --> 00:48:09.882
IPH5201 is an humanized antibody that

789
00:48:09.962 --> 00:48:13.882
blocks CD39, and by doing so, limits the conversion

790
00:48:13.902 --> 00:48:17.822
of ATP into AMP. And so ultimately, we will

791
00:48:17.962 --> 00:48:21.872
have reduced immunosuppression from adenosine with activation

792
00:48:21.902 --> 00:48:24.542
of dendritic cells and increased T cell-mediated

793
00:48:24.682 --> 00:48:26.482
cytotoxicity and tumor

794
00:48:26.522 --> 00:48:30.026
control.The preclinical

795
00:48:30.066 --> 00:48:33.746
rationale is robust. CD39 inhibition

796
00:48:34.166 --> 00:48:36.566
synergizes with chemotherapy in vivo,

797
00:48:37.406 --> 00:48:41.206
and the antitumor effect appears to be primarily mediated via

798
00:48:41.246 --> 00:48:43.186
CD8 and CD4.

799
00:48:44.646 --> 00:48:48.246
In preclinical models, the combination of CD39

800
00:48:48.266 --> 00:48:51.746
inhibition with immunotherapy and with chemoimmunotherapy

801
00:48:52.106 --> 00:48:54.966
leads to tumor eradication and improves survival.

802
00:48:56.906 --> 00:49:00.226
MATISSE is a classic signal-seeking Phase II

803
00:49:00.346 --> 00:49:04.246
trial with a design that allows to make rapid

804
00:49:04.366 --> 00:49:06.976
go/no-go decisions for clinical development.

805
00:49:08.176 --> 00:49:11.646
The primary endpoint is the pathological complete response in the resected tumor

806
00:49:11.666 --> 00:49:14.396
specimen and sample regional lymph nodes.

807
00:49:15.286 --> 00:49:19.026
The study has no power to make definitive comparison

808
00:49:19.346 --> 00:49:20.956
or for formal hypothesis testing.

809
00:49:21.316 --> 00:49:24.826
The design allows to estimate a PCR rate with an

810
00:49:24.866 --> 00:49:28.506
acceptable level of accuracy and to identify

811
00:49:28.526 --> 00:49:32.426
potential promising biological signals that can justify further

812
00:49:32.446 --> 00:49:34.466
clinical development of novel agents.

813
00:49:35.006 --> 00:49:38.646
As you heard, the target PCR rate was set at

814
00:49:38.786 --> 00:49:40.006
40% in MATISSE

815
00:49:40.886 --> 00:49:44.706
based on the benchmark of 25% with neoadjuvant chemoimmunotherapy in the

816
00:49:44.746 --> 00:49:46.006
CheckMate 816.

817
00:49:47.926 --> 00:49:51.826
The MATISSE population included patients with Stage 2, 3A disease.

818
00:49:52.446 --> 00:49:55.706
Half of those are Stage 3, and I think it will be important to

819
00:49:55.746 --> 00:49:59.326
dissect the nodal status of this population as we know that

820
00:49:59.366 --> 00:50:03.346
perioperative immunotherapy can be beneficial for patients with Stage 3

821
00:50:03.406 --> 00:50:07.026
and 2 and N1 and 2, and with single and multi-station N2

822
00:50:07.106 --> 00:50:07.526
status.

823
00:50:09.046 --> 00:50:12.966
The PD-L1 breakdown overall reflects the

824
00:50:13.006 --> 00:50:16.566
distribution of expression of this marker that we have seen across the study.

825
00:50:18.406 --> 00:50:22.046
Feasibility is a strength. Almost 85% of patients

826
00:50:22.346 --> 00:50:25.666
received the full four cycles planned in the neoadjuvant setting

827
00:50:26.326 --> 00:50:30.166
with high resectability rate, no cancellation of surgery due

828
00:50:30.226 --> 00:50:33.946
to adverse events, which is important as the addition of a

829
00:50:34.006 --> 00:50:37.226
novel agent did not compromise the surgical outcomes.

830
00:50:38.466 --> 00:50:42.286
In MATISSE, the perioperative dropout rate is lower than what

831
00:50:42.326 --> 00:50:45.886
we've seen with other perioperative trials. This is very encouraging.

832
00:50:46.346 --> 00:50:50.046
Eighty percent of patients achieved the adjuvant phase of the study.

833
00:50:50.346 --> 00:50:53.966
However, we have some limitation, limited sample size, and I think it will be

834
00:50:53.986 --> 00:50:57.686
important to better understand the features and the elements of

835
00:50:57.746 --> 00:50:59.766
completion of perioperative treatment.

836
00:51:02.786 --> 00:51:05.826
The overall PCR rate with MATISSE was

837
00:51:06.066 --> 00:51:09.436
27.5%. Looking at the PD-L1 subgroups,

838
00:51:09.646 --> 00:51:12.156
8.3% in the PD-L1 negative population,

839
00:51:12.666 --> 00:51:16.186
35.7% in the overall positive PD-L1

840
00:51:16.226 --> 00:51:19.646
subgroup, and 50% in the PD-L1

841
00:51:19.686 --> 00:51:23.626
high tumors. So clearly a signal in the PD-L1 high

842
00:51:23.706 --> 00:51:27.186
population. When we compare these rates to the AEGEAN,

843
00:51:28.046 --> 00:51:31.886
which used the backbone chemotherapy in durva, we see

844
00:51:31.946 --> 00:51:35.766
that there is an apparent increase in the PCR rate

845
00:51:35.826 --> 00:51:39.246
with MATISSE, but not all patient subgroups

846
00:51:39.946 --> 00:51:43.586
benefited the same. So you can see that perhaps the impact in

847
00:51:43.606 --> 00:51:47.586
MATISSE of IPH5201 is greater in

848
00:51:47.626 --> 00:51:50.186
the PD-L1 high population. We need to be careful.

849
00:51:50.316 --> 00:51:54.146
These are cross-trial comparisons with 40 patients in MATISSE as compared to

850
00:51:54.226 --> 00:51:57.726
more than 740 patients in the AEGEAN.

851
00:51:58.086 --> 00:52:01.506
However, if we broaden this cross-trial comparison,

852
00:52:02.066 --> 00:52:06.036
the apparent increase of PCR rate with MATISSE,

853
00:52:06.266 --> 00:52:10.236
especially if we include the CheckMate 707T perioperative strategy,

854
00:52:10.306 --> 00:52:12.036
CheckMate 816 neoadjuvant,

855
00:52:12.866 --> 00:52:16.426
it becomes less clear in the high PD-L1 population.

856
00:52:18.026 --> 00:52:18.166
So

857
00:52:19.006 --> 00:52:22.746
the question is: how does IPH5201 antitumor activity

858
00:52:22.866 --> 00:52:26.366
compare to that of other inhibitors of the ATP adenosine

859
00:52:26.466 --> 00:52:30.126
pathway tested in the perioperative setting for resectable lung cancer?

860
00:52:30.886 --> 00:52:34.546
Well, oleclumab is an anti-CD73 human monoclonal

861
00:52:34.566 --> 00:52:37.926
antibody that selectively binds to and inhibits

862
00:52:38.086 --> 00:52:41.946
CD73, and by doing so, reduces the CD73 cell

863
00:52:42.026 --> 00:52:45.986
surface expression, reduces extracellular adenosine production, and

864
00:52:46.026 --> 00:52:49.946
promotes antitumor immunity. Preclinical data have been very encouraging

865
00:52:50.006 --> 00:52:53.746
with oleclumab in mouse models and also

866
00:52:54.226 --> 00:52:57.866
in the window of opportunity trial NEOCOAST in a

867
00:52:57.906 --> 00:53:01.746
chemo-sparing neoadjuvant approach with oleclumab and durvalumab for patients with

868
00:53:01.766 --> 00:53:03.266
resectable non-small cell lung cancer.

869
00:53:04.726 --> 00:53:08.336
Perioperative oleclumab plus durvalumab and neoadjuvant

870
00:53:08.386 --> 00:53:12.086
chemotherapy have been tested in the NEOCOAST-2

871
00:53:12.166 --> 00:53:15.826
multi-arm platform study for patients with resectable non-small cell lung

872
00:53:15.906 --> 00:53:19.636
cancer. And what we have seen in NEOCOAST-2 is that the overall

873
00:53:20.146 --> 00:53:23.856
pathological complete response rate with perioperative oleclumab, durvalumab, and

874
00:53:23.856 --> 00:53:27.726
neoadjuvant chemo is 20.3%. However, not

875
00:53:27.746 --> 00:53:30.606
all patient subgroups benefit equally.

876
00:53:31.026 --> 00:53:34.526
In the PD-L1 negative population, the PCR rate with oleclumab is

877
00:53:34.566 --> 00:53:38.486
16%, in the PD-L1 high, 31%. And

878
00:53:38.506 --> 00:53:41.946
you can appreciate that the efficacy of

879
00:53:43.186 --> 00:53:47.106
MATISSE, the IPH5201, appears to be having

880
00:53:47.126 --> 00:53:49.906
greater magnitude in the PD-L1 high population.

881
00:53:50.616 --> 00:53:54.446
And so perhaps these signals tell us that while we're looking at the small

882
00:53:54.546 --> 00:53:58.526
numbers, targeting different components of the ATP

883
00:53:58.566 --> 00:54:02.166
adenosine pathway might be more beneficial specifically for

884
00:54:02.366 --> 00:54:06.136
particular type of subgroups. And so a more thoughtful

885
00:54:06.166 --> 00:54:09.366
question, perhaps, is not just to compare anti-CD73 and

886
00:54:09.386 --> 00:54:12.986
anti-CD39 therapy, but perhaps can we achieve greater

887
00:54:13.086 --> 00:54:16.866
antitumor activity and immune stimulation by blocking the multiple

888
00:54:16.906 --> 00:54:19.806
enzymatic steps of the ATP adenosine pathway?

889
00:54:20.286 --> 00:54:23.966
Well, the IPH5301 is an anti-CD73

890
00:54:24.006 --> 00:54:27.786
antibody that blocks enzyme activity of this molecule without

891
00:54:27.886 --> 00:54:29.666
causing receptor internalization.

892
00:54:29.976 --> 00:54:33.226
And so synergy of combining anti-CD39 and

893
00:54:33.266 --> 00:54:36.776
anti-CD73 therapies could be achieved via reduced

894
00:54:36.846 --> 00:54:40.426
resistance mechanisms and more robustimmune responses.

895
00:54:40.716 --> 00:54:44.466
And that's where I strongly believe the translational and biomarker

896
00:54:44.566 --> 00:54:48.046
study are critical. In MATIS, we have seen that the

897
00:54:48.146 --> 00:54:52.086
CD39 cell density in baseline tumors

898
00:54:52.366 --> 00:54:56.176
appears to be associated with pathological responses, although we are looking at

899
00:54:56.246 --> 00:55:00.166
small numbers. And while we see an enrichment of the signal

900
00:55:00.186 --> 00:55:04.006
in the PD-L1 high population with MATIS, we do not appreciate a clear

901
00:55:04.046 --> 00:55:07.936
correlation and relationship between CD39 in tumor cells and

902
00:55:07.946 --> 00:55:11.685
PD-L1 expression. And furthermore, in MATIS and in

903
00:55:11.695 --> 00:55:15.386
NEOCOST too, the amount of CD8 T-cell

904
00:55:15.446 --> 00:55:19.346
infiltrates in baseline tumor did not appear to correlate with

905
00:55:19.356 --> 00:55:23.306
efficacy. That might tell us that perhaps single T-cell infiltration might

906
00:55:23.346 --> 00:55:27.266
not be sufficient. What might possibly be more important is

907
00:55:27.306 --> 00:55:30.606
colocalization of multiple markers that can

908
00:55:30.626 --> 00:55:33.856
reflect better the nature of the immune microenvironment, and

909
00:55:33.946 --> 00:55:37.586
specifically the spatial and the functional organization of these infiltrates.

910
00:55:38.246 --> 00:55:41.686
Colocalization of CD39, CD103, and CD8 positive

911
00:55:41.766 --> 00:55:45.356
T-cells in tumor nests of early stage non-small cell lung

912
00:55:45.426 --> 00:55:47.846
cancer is associated with poor survival.

913
00:55:48.106 --> 00:55:52.026
And this might reflect perhaps an active but immunosuppressed

914
00:55:52.066 --> 00:55:55.846
immune microenvironment where combining anti-PD-L1 therapy with

915
00:55:55.866 --> 00:55:59.666
blockade of multiple steps of the adenosine pathway

916
00:55:59.686 --> 00:56:02.966
could be beneficial in a select subgroup of patients.

917
00:56:03.006 --> 00:56:06.796
My takeaways, MATIS is a well-designed, biological

918
00:56:06.906 --> 00:56:10.526
driven signal-seeking study that allows for rapid

919
00:56:10.646 --> 00:56:14.426
go/no-go decision, perhaps specifically in the PD-L1 high

920
00:56:14.546 --> 00:56:17.706
subset where the signal appears exciting.

921
00:56:17.876 --> 00:56:21.086
However, it calls for an important need for

922
00:56:21.426 --> 00:56:25.386
validation of biological drivers of efficacy to apply an

923
00:56:25.406 --> 00:56:29.046
adenosine focused strategy with multi-step inhibition in select

924
00:56:29.086 --> 00:56:32.486
subgroups. And also calls for the need of more robust,

925
00:56:32.886 --> 00:56:36.526
integrated, and dynamic biomarker studies for better patient

926
00:56:36.566 --> 00:56:38.266
selection. Thank you for your attention.

